== chmod ==
You can change file permissions with:
{{Cmd|chmod [u][g][o] [file]}}
* [u] is the number for user permissions
* [g] is the number for group permissions
* [o] is the number for other users permissions
Numbers are obtained in the following way:
* 7 = 4 + 2 + 1 (read/write/execute)
* 6 = 4 + 2 (read/write)
* 5 = 4 + 1 (read/execute)
* 4 = 4 (read)
* 3 = 2 + 1 (write/execute)
* 2 = 2 (write)
* 1 = 1 (execute)

== chown ==
You can change owner and group of file with:
{{RootCmd|chown [user]:[group] [file]}}
You can change owner of folder and files inside recursively with:
{{RootCmd|chown -R [user]:[group] [folder]}}

== gpasswd ==
You can add user to group with:
{{RootCmd|gpasswd -a [user] [group]}}
You can remove user from group with:
{{RootCmd|gpasswd -d [user] [group]}}
